text: Whitehall is a city of Trempealeau County in the state of Wisconsin, United States. It can be found along the Trempealeau River. About 1,645 people were living in Whitehall as of 2020. The cities of Arcadia, Independence, and Blair can be found nearby Whitehall. It is the county seat of Trempealeau County. == References == ==Other websites== *Whitehall Chamber of Commerce Category:County seats in Wisconsin Category:Cities in Wisconsin Category:Trempealeau County, Wisconsin
